### PUT request to update allergy severity (e.g., allergy got worse)
PUT http://localhost:4000/patients/{{patient_id}}/allergies/{{allergy_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "{{patient_id}}",
  "allergen": "Penicillin",
  "allergyType": "MEDICATION",
  "severity": "LIFE_THREATENING",
  "reaction": "Severe anaphylactic reaction, loss of consciousness, requires immediate epinephrine",
  "notes": "Allergy severity increased after recent exposure. Patient now requires immediate medical supervision if any penicillin-based medication is considered. Updated EpiPen prescription.",
  "isActive": true
}

###

### PUT request to deactivate resolved allergy
PUT http://localhost:4000/patients/{{patient_id}}/allergies/{{allergy_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "{{patient_id}}",
  "allergen": "Pollen (Ragweed)",
  "allergyType": "ENVIRONMENTAL",
  "severity": "MODERATE",
  "reaction": "Sneezing, runny nose, watery eyes, nasal congestion",
  "notes": "After immunotherapy treatment, patient no longer experiences significant reactions. Monitoring for one more season before considering fully resolved.",
  "isActive": false
}

